Frequently Asked Questions

What does SysTracker do?
SysTracker provides real-time system monitoring for iPhone and iPad, including CPU activity, memory usage, GPU activity, storage, network activity, and battery information, all presented in a clean and easy-to-read interface.

Does SysTracker collect or share my data?
No. SysTracker runs entirely on your device. No personal data, system metrics, or usage information is collected, stored, or shared with external servers.

Does the app affect battery life?
SysTracker is designed to be efficient and lightweight. System data is refreshed at practical intervals, and the interface is optimized to minimize battery impact during normal use.

Why are some values estimated?
Because of iOS platform limitations, some low-level system information is not exposed directly to third-party apps. In those cases, SysTracker displays the most accurate values possible using available Apple-supported APIs.

Does SysTracker work on iPad?
Yes. SysTracker is optimized for both iPhone and iPad, with layouts that adapt to different screen sizes.

What version of iOS is required?
SysTracker requires iOS 17.0 or later.

Troubleshooting

The app is not showing data
Close and reopen the app. If the issue continues, restart your device and launch SysTracker again.

Charts or values are not updating
Make sure the app is open and active in the foreground. iOS limits certain live monitoring behavior when apps are not actively in use.

The app crashed or became unresponsive
Please update to the latest version available on the App Store. If the issue continues, contact support with your device model and iOS version.

